The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Tuesday, November 02, 2004 

 Arafat plea

 Paris, Nov. 1 (Reuters): Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat condemned a suicide bombing in Tel Aviv today and called on both Palestinians and Israelis to avoid killing civilians, a senior aide said.

 ?He (Arafat) condemned the attack in Tel Aviv and said that he condemns the killing of civilians on both sides,? senior aide Nabil Abu Rdainah said in Paris after he received a phone call from the Palestinian leader. Three persons were killed in the boming.




